-8- Spot 5 Orcs to stop the Freeps <br>
-9- Tol Brandir<br>
<br>
PLEASE READ STRATEGY BEFORE RATING!!!   THANX!!!!<br>
<br>
<br>
FREEPS: <br>
---------<br>
  Bid 1! If you can choose to go first, but normally you won&#39;t. If he starts Pony start Merry and Boromir, if he doesn&#39;t i suggest you also start them, cuz there is only 1 copy of them.<br>
<br>
Basically the Freeps ain&#39;t hard to play, there are just some nice things i have to stress. Boromir + Blade of Gondor + Saga is the ultimate Uruk Killa!!! As is Frodo when equipped with his beloved pan! <br>
<br>
I know most people are saying that Moria is Choke&#39;s death but with 4 PATHS and Frodp with the Pan it is quite difficult to kill him. Nazghul won&#39;t be a problem, cuz they are too expensive to play, and if they come out you can beat em with gorn +1 sword + Brand and cancel the fierce skirmish with Bolger! The only nazghul that might bring you into trouble is Cantea, but (it depends on the Situation) there are ways round it, e.g. On direct shot + 1 PATHS and take the wound, but beware of All blades perish, always think of it and have a second option! <br>
Mordor isn&#39;t too hard, cuz they won&#39;t get out any threatening Minions until site 6 and they will eventually have their hand clogged with shadow cards and so you will have a fair chance killing frodo. <br>
Uruk-Hai aren&#39;t to tough either, just saruman is a pain in the eye, but there are ways round it 2!<br>
If there are many uruk players in your meta, maybe add some ARV to arv saruman, so he can&#39;t prevent wounds from the Blade of Gondor,Aragorn&#39;s Bow or PATHS. Normally the Uruk player won&#39;t have the Twilight to play Saruman + many minions. <br>
<br>
Now I have to talk about one of the most important cards: DEFT IN THEIR MOVEMENTS!! When your fellowship phase starts you have to be almost completely sure about doblemoving or not! That&#39;s the point when you have to decide if you are healing Boromir AND playing some stuff or just playing or just healing etc. If you plan to make a double move do not spend more than 2 twilight in your fellowship Phase and maybe have a DEFT in your Hand!<br>
<br>
Ok, that&#39;s about the Freeps.<br>
<br>
Shadow:<br>
-------<br>
 Satrt playing DDotR an their main characters to make him get some burdens. If he gets rid of em you still have one of my favorite minions: ORC PILLAGER! ´The more the character  wears the less power he has, thats just great. Also i still love Hate! That&#39;s the card ther is NO WAY ROUND IT!!! <br>
And hate works perfectly with Orc Overseer!<br>
Against these trust me deck you may be able to finish Gandalf of early in the Game, you his trust me is worthless, but don&#39;t hesitate to kill any other comanion. If you don&#39;t know what i mean, read &quot;The Importance of a Dead Companion&quot;.<br>
<br>
The One Gleaming to the snow might be the crucial card in the late game, give him burdens, so <br>
e.g: you can overwhelm with the enduring evils<br>
     you can use Enquea ( with this guy you      practically have 7 hates)  etc<br>
<br>
OK...thats it.<br>
I hope you enjoy playing and your partys!<br>
HAVE FUN<br>
